Anne Dudek https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anne_Dudek 0 Anne Louise Dudek (born March 22, 1975) is an American actress. She is known for portraying Tiffany Wilson in the 2004 film White Chicks, Danielle Brookson in the USA Network television series Covert Affairs, Dr. Amber Volakis on the Fox series House, Lura Grant on the HBO series Big Love, and Francine Hanson on the AMC series Mad Men. She has also starred in the British television series The Book Group. Anne_Louise_Dudek ( born March_22_,_1975 ) is an_American_actress .
